{
  "id": "present-tense",
  "title": "Present Tense Verbs",
  "order": 4,
  "summary": "Most Catalan verbs follow predictable conjugation patterns in the present tense.",
  "sections": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": "Catalan verbs are grouped into three conjugation classes based on their infinitive ending: -ar (most common), -er/-re, and -ir. The good news: within each group the pattern is consistent, so once you learn the pattern you can conjugate hundreds of verbs."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": "Unlike English, Catalan verb endings carry the subject — so the pronoun is often dropped. 'Parlo' means 'I speak' by itself; you don't need 'jo' unless you're emphasising."
    },
    {
      "type": "rule",
      "content": "-AR verbs (e.g. parlar = to speak): drop -ar, add endings: -o, -es, -a, -em, -eu, -en"
    },
    {
      "type": "examples",
      "items": [
        {
          "catalan": "parlo",
          "english": "I speak",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "parles",
          "english": "you speak",
          "note": "informal singular"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "parla",
          "english": "he/she speaks",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "parlem",
          "english": "we speak",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "parleu",
          "english": "you speak",
          "note": "plural / formal"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "parlen",
          "english": "they speak",
          "note": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "rule",
      "content": "-ER/-RE verbs (e.g. córrer = to run): drop -er/-re, add: -o, -s, (nothing), -em, -eu, -en"
    },
    {
      "type": "examples",
      "items": [
        {
          "catalan": "corro",
          "english": "I run",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "corres",
          "english": "you run",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "corre",
          "english": "he/she runs",
          "note": "3rd person singular: no extra ending"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "correm",
          "english": "we run",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "correu",
          "english": "you run",
          "note": "plural"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "corren",
          "english": "they run",
          "note": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "rule",
      "content": "-IR verbs (e.g. dormir = to sleep): drop -ir, add: -o, -s, (nothing), -im, -iu, -en. Some -ir verbs insert -eix- in singular and 3rd plural forms."
    },
    {
      "type": "examples",
      "items": [
        {
          "catalan": "dormo",
          "english": "I sleep",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "dorms",
          "english": "you sleep",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "dorm",
          "english": "he/she sleeps",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "dormim",
          "english": "we sleep",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "dormiu",
          "english": "you sleep",
          "note": "plural"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "dormen",
          "english": "they sleep",
          "note": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": "Some very common verbs are irregular and must be memorised individually: ser (to be), estar (to be), tenir (to have), anar (to go), fer (to do/make), poder (to be able to), voler (to want). You've already seen ser and estar."
    },
    {
      "type": "examples",
      "items": [
        {
          "catalan": "tinc / tens / té / tenim / teniu / tenen",
          "english": "I have / you have / he has...",
          "note": "tenir — irregular"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "vaig / vas / va / anem / aneu / van",
          "english": "I go / you go / he goes...",
          "note": "anar — highly irregular"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "faig / fas / fa / fem / feu / fan",
          "english": "I do / you do / he does...",
          "note": "fer — irregular"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "practice": [
    {
      "id": "pt-p01",
      "kind": "multiple_choice",
      "question": "'Parlar' means 'to speak'. How do you say 'she speaks'?",
      "options": [
        "parla",
        "parles",
        "parlo",
        "parlen"
      ],
      "answer": "parla",
      "explanation": "-ar 3sg → -a."
    },
    {
      "id": "pt-p02",
      "kind": "multiple_choice",
      "question": "How do you say 'we sleep' using 'dormir'?",
      "options": [
        "dormim",
        "dormem",
        "dormo",
        "dormen"
      ],
      "answer": "dormim",
      "explanation": "-ir 1pl → -im."
    },
    {
      "id": "pt-p03",
      "kind": "multiple_choice",
      "question": "In Catalan, do you need the subject pronoun 'jo' (I) to mean 'I speak'?",
      "options": [
        "No — 'parlo' already means 'I speak'",
        "Yes — you must say 'jo parlo'"
      ],
      "answer": "No — 'parlo' already means 'I speak'",
      "explanation": "Ending encodes subject."
    },
    {
      "id": "pt-p04",
      "kind": "multiple_choice",
      "question": "How do you say 'I have' using 'tenir'?",
      "options": [
        "tinc",
        "tens",
        "té",
        "tenim"
      ],
      "answer": "tinc",
      "explanation": "tenir 1sg irregular: tinc."
    },
    {
      "id": "pt-p05",
      "kind": "cloze",
      "prompt": "Nosaltres ___ català. (parlar)",
      "hint": "we speak",
      "answer": "parlem",
      "explanation": "-ar 1pl → -em."
    },
    {
      "id": "pt-p06",
      "kind": "cloze",
      "prompt": "Ell ___ ràpid. (córrer)",
      "hint": "he runs",
      "answer": "corre",
      "explanation": "-re 3sg keeps stem."
    },
    {
      "id": "pt-p07",
      "kind": "cloze",
      "prompt": "Jo ___ a casa. (anar)",
      "hint": "I go",
      "answer": "vaig",
      "explanation": "anar irregular: vaig."
    },
    {
      "id": "pt-p08",
      "kind": "type_in",
      "prompt": "I speak",
      "answers": [
        "parlo",
